{"questionId":"22581033","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the equation of the line through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to divide their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;by their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;substitute into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>e.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>÷</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;equivalent manipulation leading to given answer&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0 FT</strong></em> if their answer does not lead to the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,</p>\n<p>so equation is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <em><strong>M1A0</strong></em> for working backwards to verify points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> lie on the given line.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22581033","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ1.2g","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that the equation of the line through B and C is y=-m38+nx.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"g","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}